The paper discusses a python toolbox for dealing with imbalanced datasets in machine learning, which is a common problem in various subfields of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these subfields frequently encounter imbalanced datasets. The paper may also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these subfields may also encounter imbalanced datasets in certain applications.
